              safely.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 2 -->
        <div
          class="feature-card rounded-lg p-6"
          style="background-color: #102951;"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-3">
            <div class="p-3 rounded-full bg-blue-500 bg-opacity-20">
              <svg
                class="w-10 h-10"
                style="color: #dda853;"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              >
                <!-- Shield with Checkmark -->
                <path
                  d="M12 2L3 7v6c0 5.1 3.78 9.84 9 10.5 5.22-.66 9-5.4 9-10.5V7l-9-5z"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-width="1.5"></path>
                <path
                  d="M8 11l3 3 5-5"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">
              Approval Flow for Queries
            </h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-white text-opacity-90 mb-4 font-light text-lg">
            Because production data deserves a second set of eyes.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="text-white text-opacity-80 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5 font-light"
          >
            <li>Two-key security for your queries.</li>
            <li>No more cowboy SQL in prod.</li>
            <li>
              Most tools obsess over dashboards—we obsess over ops sanity.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 3 -->
        <div
          class="feature-card rounded-lg p-6"
          style="background-color: #102951;"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-3">
            <div class="p-3 rounded-full bg-blue-500 bg-opacity-20">
              <svg
                class="w-10 h-10"
                style="color: #dda853;"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
